3. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper leverages the power of deep neural networks to improve RL performance, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The experiments are conducted on Atari games, which are visual environments, and the proposed algorithm uses convolutional neural networks to process the visual input.
